WEBVTT

00:00.537 --> 00:04.743
The Farmer's Cursed Wife.

00:05.684 --> 00:08.628
There was no man who owned a farm.

00:08.888 --> 00:11.451
Hi, hi, diddle-um-day.

00:11.912 --> 00:17.539
There was no man who owned a farm, and he had no cattle to carry it on.

00:17.559 --> 00:21.284
Singing twice, fi-dum, fi-diddle, fi-dum, fi-day.

00:21.905 --> 00:25.009
He yoked two pigs in order to plow.

00:25.073 --> 00:27.919
Hi, hi, diddle-um-day.

00:28.359 --> 00:31.005
He yoked two pigs in order to plow.

00:31.405 --> 00:34.311
And if he did it, the devil knows how.

00:34.331 --> 00:38.038
Singing twice, fi-dum, fi-diddle, fi-dum, fi-day.

00:38.680 --> 00:41.445
The devil came to him in the field one day.

00:41.560 --> 00:44.144
Hi, hi, diddle-um-day.

00:44.684 --> 00:47.188
The devil came to him in the field one day.

00:47.248 --> 00:49.892
Said, one of your family I will carry away.

00:50.452 --> 00:54.057
Singing twice, fi dum, fi diddle, fi dum, fi day.

00:54.899 --> 00:57.402
You can't have my oldest son.

00:57.782 --> 01:00.326
Hi, hi, diddle-um-day.

01:00.967 --> 01:03.410
You can't have my oldest son.

01:03.470 --> 01:06.655
For the work of the farm must still go on.

01:06.675 --> 01:10.420
Singing twice, fi dum, fi diddle, fi dum, fi day.

01:11.530 --> 01:17.397
You can have my scolding wife, hi, hi, diddle-um-day.

01:17.437 --> 01:23.484
You can have my scolding wife, but you can't keep her to save your life.

01:23.845 --> 01:27.629
Singing twice, fi dum, fi diddle, fi dum, fi day.

01:28.210 --> 01:34.197
The devil packed her up in a sack, hi, hi, diddle-um-day.

